<HEAD>Sihanouk Says Would Meet Vietnamese-backed Cambodian Leader</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Prince <PERSON> Norodom </PERSON> <PERSON> Sihanouk </PERSON>, leader of a <LOCATION> Cambodian </LOCATION> resistance coalition, said Sunday he has agreed to meet <PERSON> Hun </PERSON> <PERSON> Sen </PERSON>, prime minister of <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION>'s Vietnamese-backed government. In a statement released from his residence in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Sihanouk </PERSON> said he had been informed by a <LOCATION> French </LOCATION> diplomat that <PERSON> Hun </PERSON> <PERSON> Sen </PERSON> was ready to make `` two concessions in regard to the problem in <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION>.'' He did not reveal the nature of the concessions. He said the meeting of <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION>'s four warring factions could take place as early as May 2 in <LOCATION> Indonesia </LOCATION> or in September in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>. Last month <PERSON> Hun </PERSON> <PERSON> Sen </PERSON> sent a letter to <PERSON> Sihanouk </PERSON> saying `` there are elements that show that a fundamental agreement is possible'' between the government and resistance groups. <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> invaded <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION> in December 1978, drove out the radical <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION> regime that defeated the U.S.-backed government in the spring of 1975, and installed another communist administration. Hundreds of thousands of Cambodians were killed during the nearly three years the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION> was in power as it purged opponents and drove people out of the cities to impose a harsh form of agrarian communism. <PERSON> Prince </PERSON> <PERSON> Sihanouk </PERSON>, who was deposed in 1970, now leads a resistance alliance of his supporters, the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION> and Cambodians loyal to anti-communist <LOCATION> Son </LOCATION> <LOCATION> San </LOCATION>. The three alliance m