te beverage. <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> has championed an anti-alcoholism campaign in the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> and has severely restricted sales of vodka. <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> and <PERSON> Haughey </PERSON>, surrounded by their foreign ministers and aides, met in a VIP lounge. Outside hung a vast oil painting of the late <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON> that commemorated a 1963 visit by the Irish-American president shortly before his assassination.
